!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

encounter /ɪnˈkaʊntə/

(encountering,encountered,encounters) 

1. V-T If you encounter problems or difficulties, you experience them. 遭遇 

例： Every day of our lives we encounter major and minor stresses of one kind or another. 生活中的每一天，我们会遇到或大或小的这样那样的压力。 

2. V-T If you encounter someone, you meet them, usually unexpectedly. 邂逅 [正式] 

例： Did you encounter anyone in the building? 你在那栋大楼里偶然遇到什么人了吗？ 

3. N-COUNT An encounter with someone is a meeting with them, particularly one that is unexpected or significant. 邂逅 

例： The author tells of a remarkable encounter with a group of South Vietnamese soldiers. 作者讲述了他与一群南越士兵的惊人邂逅。 

4. N-COUNT An encounter is a particular type of experience. 特殊经历 

例： ...a sexual encounter. …一次性经历。

